hey! welcome to my space! here are some (random?) facts about me (˵ •̀ ᴗ - ˵ ) ✧

i’m nic(holas), but i go online by kdo (short for my real name).

i love reading, traveling, listening to music, observing surroundings, and learning new things 👀. you can usually find me taking long walks, sitting in a coffee shop all day, and trying to craft a random idea out of my head. sometimes, i just love to go around and try new things at every opportunity while pushing myself out of my comfort zone ˙✧˖°📷 ༘ ⋆｡˚.

also, i like to learn as much as i can from the amazing people around me so plz connect!!! (˶˃ ᵕ ˂˶)

I learned how to code while thinking about how to turn a random Lego into a personal assistant. I’ve dabbled in digital media, healthcare, and fintech, building different digital apps and initiatives to help people in my community and beyond. I love to create meaningful technologies that change the world and make life easier. ‧₊˚🖇️✩ ₊˚🎧⊹♡


currently

i'm a sophomore at{" "} UNC-Chapel Hill , working on my {" "} computer science 🧑🏻‍💻 and{" "} {mymajors} degree! 🩵

i’m interested in human-computer interaction 🗯, and all creative intersections of tech, media, and healthcare. my research interests are in machine learning, natural language processing, computer vision. however, I’m always open to exploring new and exciting opportunities. ﮩـﮩﮩ٨ـ♡ﮩ٨ـﮩﮩ٨ـ


previously

did some internships & research

  • created websites for non-profits ( Develop for Good )
  • analyzed sentiments of historical contents ( Denison Digital Humanities )
  • developed financial dashboards and deployed sap systems ( Grant Thornton Vietnam )
  • worked full-stack on a travelling app ( Campdi )
  • worked on new game features for vietnam’s largest streaming platform ( FPT Play )

some clubs
